quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  34,46,"Say, ‘I give you just a single advice: that you rise up for Allah’s sake, in pairs or singly, and then reflect: there is no madness in your companion; he is just a warner to you before [the befalling of] a severe punishment.’"
  34,47,"Say, ‘Whatever reward I may have asked you is for your own good. My [true] reward lies only with Allah, and He is witness to all things.’"
  34,48,"Say, ‘Indeed my Lord hurls the truth. [He is] the knower of all that is Unseen.’"
  34,49,"Say, ‘The truth has come, and falsehood neither originates nor restores [anything].’"
  34,50,"Say, ‘If I go astray, my going astray is only to my own harm, and if I am rightly guided that is because of what my Lord has revealed to me. Indeed He is all-hearing and nearmost.’"
  34,51,"Were you to see them when they will be stricken with terror, without any escape, and are seized from a close quarter"
  34,52,"They will say, ‘We believe in it [now]!’ But how can they attain it from a far-off place"
  34,53,when they denied it in the past—shooting at something invisible from a far-off place—
  34,54,"and a barrier is set between them and what they desire, as was done aforetime with their likes, who had remained in grave doubt"